#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.23:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "3. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Kāyasutta "
msgstr "23. Body "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.39, sc1
msgctxt "an10.23:1.1"
msgid "“Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā kāyena pahātabbā, no vācāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are things that should be given up by the body, not by speech. "

msgctxt "an10.23:1.2"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā vācāya pahātabbā, no kāyena. "
msgstr "There are things that should be given up by speech, not by the body. "

#. VAR: paññāya disvā → disvā disvā (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an10.23:1.3"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, dhammā neva kāyena pahātabbā no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbā. "
msgstr "There are things that should be given up neither by the body, nor by speech, but by seeing again and again with wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an10.23:2.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā kāyena pahātabbā, no vācāya? "
msgstr "And what are the things that should be given up by the body, not by speech? "

#. VAR: āpanno hoti kiñci desaṃ → kañcideva desaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.23:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akusalaṃ āpanno hoti kiñci desaṃ kāyena. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has committed a certain unskillful offense by way of body. "

msgctxt "an10.23:2.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ anuvicca viññū sabrahmacārī evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "After examination, sensible spiritual companions say this to them: "

msgctxt "an10.23:2.4"
msgid "‘āyasmā kho akusalaṃ āpanno kiñci desaṃ kāyena. "
msgstr "‘Venerable, you’ve committed a certain unskillful offense by way of body. "

msgctxt "an10.23:2.5"
msgid "Sādhu vatāyasmā kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāvetū’ti. "
msgstr "Please give up that bad bodily conduct and develop good bodily conduct.’ "

msgctxt "an10.23:2.6"
msgid "So anuvicca viññūhi sabrahmacārīhi vuccamāno kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "When spoken to by their sensible spiritual companions they give up that bad bodily conduct and develop good bodily conduct. "

msgctxt "an10.23:2.7"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā kāyena pahātabbā, no vācāya. "
msgstr "These are the things that should be given up by the body, not by speech. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.23:3.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā vācāya pahātabbā, no kāyena? "
msgstr "And what are the things that should be given up by speech, not by the body? "

msgctxt "an10.23:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akusalaṃ āpanno hoti kiñci desaṃ vācāya. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has committed a certain unskillful offense by way of speech. "

msgctxt "an10.23:3.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ anuvicca viññū sabrahmacārī evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "After examination, sensible spiritual companions say this to them: "

msgctxt "an10.23:3.4"
msgid "‘āyasmā kho akusalaṃ āpanno kiñci desaṃ vācāya. "
msgstr "‘Venerable, you’ve committed a certain unskillful offense by way of speech. "

msgctxt "an10.23:3.5"
msgid "Sādhu vatāyasmā vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāvetū’ti. "
msgstr "Please give up that bad verbal conduct and develop good verbal conduct.’ "

msgctxt "an10.23:3.6"
msgid "So anuvicca viññūhi sabrahmacārīhi vuccamāno vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "When spoken to by their sensible spiritual companions they give up that bad verbal conduct and develop good verbal conduct. "

msgctxt "an10.23:3.7"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā vācāya pahātabbā, no kāyena. "
msgstr "These are the things that should be given up by speech, not by the body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.40, sc4
msgctxt "an10.23:4.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā neva kāyena pahātabbā no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbā? "
msgstr "And what are the things that should be given up neither by the body, nor by speech, but by seeing again and again with wisdom? "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.2"
msgid "Lobho, bhikkhave, neva kāyena pahātabbo no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbo. "
msgstr "Greed … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.3"
msgid "Doso, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "hate … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.4"
msgid "moho … "
msgstr "delusion … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.5"
msgid "kodho … "
msgstr "anger … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.6"
msgid "upanāho … "
msgstr "hostility … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.7"
msgid "makkho … "
msgstr "offensiveness … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.8"
msgid "paḷāso … "
msgstr "contempt … "

msgctxt "an10.23:4.9"
msgid "macchariyaṃ, bhikkhave, neva kāyena pahātabbaṃ no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbaṃ. "
msgstr "and stinginess are things that should be given up neither by the body, nor by speech, but by seeing again and again with wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an10.23:5.1"
msgid "Pāpikā, bhikkhave, issā neva kāyena pahātabbā no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbā. "
msgstr "Nasty jealousy should be given up neither by the body, nor by speech, but by seeing again and again with wisdom. "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.2"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, pāpikā issā? "
msgstr "And what is nasty jealousy? "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ijjhati gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā. "
msgstr "It’s when a householder or their child is prospering in money, grain, silver, or gold. "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.4"
msgid "Tatrāññatarassa dāsassa vā upavāsassa vā evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And a bondservant or dependent thinks: "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.5"
msgid "‘aho vatimassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā na ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh, may that householder or their child not prosper in money, grain, silver, or gold!’ "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.6"
msgid "Samaṇo vā pana brāhmaṇo vā lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ. "
msgstr "Or an ascetic or brahmin receives robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.7"
msgid "Tatrāññatarassa samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And some other ascetic or brahmin thinks: "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.8"
msgid "‘aho vata ayamāyasmā na lābhī assa cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh, may that ascetic or brahmin not receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.’ "

msgctxt "an10.23:5.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, pāpikā issā. "
msgstr "This is called nasty jealousy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.41, sc6
msgctxt "an10.23:6.1"
msgid "Pāpikā, bhikkhave, icchā neva kāyena pahātabbā no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbā. "
msgstr "Corrupt wishes should be given up neither by the body, nor by speech, but by seeing again and again with wisdom. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.2"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, pāpikā icchā? "
msgstr "And what are corrupt wishes? "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco assaddho samāno ‘saddhoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "It’s when a faithless person wishes to be known as faithful. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.4"
msgid "dussīlo samāno ‘sīlavāti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "An unethical person wishes to be known as ethical. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.5"
msgid "appassuto samāno ‘bahussutoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "An uneducated person wishes to be known as learned. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.6"
msgid "saṅgaṇikārāmo samāno ‘pavivittoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "A lover of company wishes to be known as secluded. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.7"
msgid "kusīto samāno ‘āraddhavīriyoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "A lazy person wishes to be known as energetic. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.8"
msgid "muṭṭhassati samāno ‘upaṭṭhitassatīti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "An unmindful person wishes to be known as mindful. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.9"
msgid "asamāhito samāno ‘samāhitoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "A person without immersion wishes to be known as having immersion. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.10"
msgid "duppañño samāno ‘paññavāti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati; "
msgstr "A witless person wishes to be known as wise. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.11"
msgid "akhīṇāsavo samāno ‘khīṇāsavoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti icchati. "
msgstr "A person who has not ended the defilements wishes to be known as having ended the defilements. "

msgctxt "an10.23:6.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, pāpikā icchā. "
msgstr "These are called corrupt wishes. "

# NOTE: Most manuscripts, followed PTS and BB, have this reading.
msgctxt "an10.23:6.13"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, dhammā neva kāyena pahātabbā no vācāya, paññāya disvā pahātabbā. "
msgstr "Corrupt wishes should be given up neither by the body, nor by speech, but by seeing again and again with wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
